place.name: FRITTON
place.gazetteerText: FRITTON, a parish in Depwade district, Norfolk; 3½ miles E by S of Forncett r. station, and 6½ N of Harleston. Post town, Long Stratton. Acres, 889. Real property, £1, 974. Pop., 235. Houses, 52. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £257. Patron, Edward Howes, Esq. The church is good; and there are a national school and townlands £34. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
